===As sideman===
In addition to songwriting, arranging, and producing, Dixon also contributed to recording sessions on double bass.&lt;ref name=&quot;amg&quot; /&gt;  However, as electric bass became dominant in the 1960s, his role as a sideman declined.&lt;ref name=&quot;amg&quot; /&gt;  Albums which contain some songs he recorded (along with other bassists) include:

[[Chuck Berry]]
* ''[[After School Session]]'' (Chess, 1957)
* ''[[One Dozen Berrys]]'' (Chess, 1958)
* ''[[Chuck Berry Is on Top]]'' (Chess, 1959)
* ''[[Rockin' at the Hops]]'' (Chess, 1960)
* ''[[St. Louis to Liverpool]]'' (Chess, 1964)
[[Bo Diddley]]
* ''[[Bo Diddley (1958 album)|Bo Diddley]] (Chess, 1958)
* ''[[Go Bo Diddley]]'' (Checker, 1959)
* ''[[Have Guitar Will Travel (Bo Diddley album)|Have Guitar Will Travel]]'' (Checker, 1960)
* ''[[Bo Diddley Is a Gunslinger]]'' (Checker, 1960)
* ''[[Bo Diddley (1962 album)|Bo Diddley]]'' (Checker, 1962)
* ''[[His Best (Bo Diddley album)|His Best]]'' (Chess/MCA, 1997)
[[Fleetwood Mac]] with [[Otis Spann]], [[Buddy Guy]], et al.
* ''[[Fleetwood Mac in Chicago]]'' ([[Blue Horizon (record label)|Blue Horizon]], 1969)
[[Howlin' Wolf]]
* ''[[Moanin' in the Moonlight]]'' (Chess, 1959)
* ''[[Howlin' Wolf (album)|Howlin' Wolf]]'' (Chess, 1962)
*''[[The Real Folk Blues (Howlin' Wolf album)|The Real Folk Blues]]'' (Chess, 1956-64 [1965])
*''[[More Real Folk Blues (Howlin' Wolf album)|More Real Folk Blues]]'' (Chess, 1953-56 [1967])
* ''[[His Best (Howlin' Wolf album)|His Best]]'' (Chess/MCA, 1997)
[[Sam Lazar]]
* ''[[Space Flight (album)|Space Flight]]'' (Argo, 1960)
[[Little Walter]]
* ''[[Best of Little Walter]]'' (Chess, 1958)
* ''[[His Best (Little Walter album)|His Best]]'' (Chess/MCA, 1997)
[[Jimmy Rogers]]
* ''[[Jimmy Rogers (album)|Jimmy Rogers]]'' (Chess, 1984)
